@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <div class="card shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body">

            <h1 class="text-center mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>

            <p class="text-muted text-center">
                IRP Integrated Resource and Procurement Management System
            </p>

            <hr />

            <h5>1. Introduction</h5>
            <p>
                The IRP Integrated Resource and Procurement Management System is committed to
                protecting the privacy and personal information of its users. This Privacy Policy
                explains how information is collected, used, stored, and protected within the system.
            </p>

            <h5>2. Information Collected</h5>
            <p>
                The system may collect personal and operational information including, but not limited to:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>User names and email addresses</li>
                <li>User roles and access permissions</li>
                <li>Procurement requests, approvals, and transaction records</li>
                <li>Inventory and resource management data</li>
            </ul>

            <h5>3. Use of Information</h5>
            <p>
                Collected information is used strictly for official purposes such as managing resources,
                processing procurement requests, monitoring inventory, and maintaining system security.
                The data supports transparency, accountability, and efficient barangay operations.
            </p>

            <h5>4. Data Security</h5>
            <p>
                Appropriate security measures are implemented to protect information against unauthorized
                access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Access to data is limited based on assigned
                user roles such as Super Admin, Chairman, Treasurer, and Staff.
            </p>

            <h5>5. Data Sharing</h5>
            <p>
                Information stored in the system is not shared with external parties unless required by law
                or authorized by barangay officials for official government purposes.
            </p>

            <h5>6. User Responsibilities</h5>
            <p>
                Users are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their login credentials and
                for ensuring that system access is used only for authorized and lawful activities.
            </p>

            <h5>7. Changes to This Policy</h5>
            <p>
                This Privacy Policy may be updated as needed to reflect changes in system functionality,
                legal requirements, or barangay policies. Users will be informed of significant updates.
            </p>

            <h5>8. Contact Information</h5>
            <p>
                For questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact the barangay
                administration or system administrator.
            </p>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>
